README.md

Awesome Pyramid

   [https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome]Awesome
   [https://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=pyramid]IRC Freenode

   A curated list of awesome Pyramid apps, projects and resources.
   Inspired by and based on
   [https://github.com/vinta/awesome-python/]awesome-python.
     * Awesome Pyramid
          + Admin Interface
          + Asset Management
          + Async
          + Authentication
          + Authorization
          + Caching & Session
          + Debugging
          + Email
          + Forms
          + Media-Management
          + RESTful API
          + Search
          + Security
          + Services
          + Settings
          + Storage
          + Task Queue
          + Testing
          + Translations
          + Web frontend integration
          + Workflows
          + Other
     * Projects
          + Framework
          + CMS
          + Cookiecutters
          + e-Commerce
          + Project Management
          + Other
     * Resources
          + Books
          + Websites
          + Conferences
          + Videos
          + Who uses it?
     * Contributing

Admin interface

   Packages that extend the Admin interface, adding or improving features.
     * [https://github.com/FormAlchemy/pyramid_formalchemy]pyramid_formalc
       hemy - provides a CRUD interface for pyramid based on FormAlchemy.
     * [https://github.com/sacrud/pyramid_sacrud]pyramid_sacrud - Pyramid
       CRUD interface. Provides an administration web interface for
       Pyramid. Unlike classic CRUD, pyramid_sacrud allows overrides and
       flexibility to customize your interface, similar to
       django.contrib.admin but uses a different backend to provide
       resources.
       [http://pyramid-sacrud.readthedocs.io/pages/contribute/architecture
       .html]New Architecture built on the resources and mechanism
       traversal, allows to use it in various cases.
          + [https://github.com/sacrud/ps_alchemy]ps_alchemy - extension
            for pyramid_sacrud which provides SQLAlchemy models.
          + [https://github.com/sacrud/ps_tree]ps_tree - extension for
            [https://github.com/sacrud/pyramid_sacrud]pyramid_sacrud which
            displays a list of records as tree. This works fine with
            models from
            [https://github.com/uralbash/sqlalchemy_mptt]sqlalchemy_mptt.
     * [https://websauna.org/docs/]Websauna - a full stack application
       framework for Pyramid

Asset Management

   Packages that help manage the static assets of a project.
     * [https://github.com/sontek/pyramid_webassets]pyramid_webassets -
       Pyramid extension for working with the webassets library.
     * [https://github.com/mrijken/pyramid_bowerstatic]pyramid_bowerstatic
       - integration of Bowerstatic in Pyramid

Async

     * [https://github.com/housleyjk/aiopyramid]aiopyramid - Run pyramid
       using asyncio.
     * [https://github.com/abourget/gevent-socketio]gevent-socketio -
       gevent-socketio is a Python implementation of the Socket.IO
       protocol, developed originally for Node.js by LearnBoost and then
       ported to other languages.
     * [https://github.com/boothead/stargate]Stargate - Stargate is a
       package for adding WebSockets support to pyramid applications using
       the excellent eventlet library for long running connections.
     * [https://github.com/AppEnlight/channelstream]channelstream -
       websocket communication server (gevent).

Authentication

   Packages that improve or extend the authentication methods of Pyramid.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_ldap]pyramid_ldap - an LDAP
       authentication policy for Pyramid.
     * [https://github.com/Cito/pyramid_ldap3]pyramid_ldap3 - Provides
       LDAP authentication services for your Pyramid application based on
       the ldap3 package.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_who]pyramid_who - Authentication
       policy for pyramid using repoze.who 2.0 API.
     * [https://github.com/bbangert/velruse]velruse - Simplifying
       third-party authentication for web applications. it supports most
       of auth
       [https://github.com/bbangert/velruse/tree/master/velruse/providers]
       providers.
     * [https://github.com/thruflo/pyramid_simpleauth]pyramid_simpleauth -
       session based authentication and role based security for Pyramid
       application
     * [https://github.com/omab/python-social-auth]Python Social Auth -
       Social authentication/registration mechanism with support for a
       large number of
       [https://github.com/omab/python-social-auth#auth-providers]provider
       s.
     * [https://github.com/authomatic/authomatic]Authomatic - Simple yet
       powerful authorization / authentication client library for Python
       web applications.
     * [https://github.com/cd34/apex]apex - Toolkit for Pyramid, a Pylons
       Project, to add Authentication and Authorization using Velruse
       (OAuth) and/or a local database, CSRF, ReCaptcha, Sessions, Flash
       messages and I18N.
     * [https://github.com/usingnamespace/pyramid_authsanity]pyramid_auths
       anity - That will make it simpler to have a secure authentication
       policy with an easy to use backend.
     * [https://github.com/wichert/pyramid_jwt]pyramid_jwt - This package
       implements an authentication policy for Pyramid that using
       [https://jwt.io/]JSON Web Tokens. This standard
       ([https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519]RFC 7519) is often used to
       secure backens APIs. The excellent
       [https://pyjwt.readthedocs.io/en/latest/]PyJWT library is used for
       the JWT encoding / decoding logic.
     * [https://github.com/mozilla-services/pyramid_ipauth]pyramid_ipauth
       - Pyramid authentication policy based on remote ip address.

Authorization

   Packages related to authorization infrastructure and permissions.
     * [https://github.com/ergo/ziggurat_foundations]ziggurat_foundations
       - Framework agnostic set of sqlalchemy classes that make building
       applications that require permissions an easy task.
     * [https://github.com/mozilla-services/pyramid_multiauth]pyramid_mult
       iauth - An authentication policy for Pyramid that proxies to a
       stack of other authentication policies.
     * [https://github.com/wichert/pyramid_authstack]pyramid_authstack -
       Use multiple authentication policies with Pyramid.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/horus]horus - User registration and
       login system for the Pyramid Web Framework.
     * [https://github.com/YosaiProject/pyramid_yosai]pyramid_yosai -
       Pyramid integration with security Framework for Python applications
       featuring Authorization (rbac permissions and roles),
       Authentication (2fa totp), Session Management and an extensive
       Audit Trail
       [https://yosaiproject.github.io/yosai/]https://yosaiproject.github.
       io/yosai/

Caching & Session

   Packages that help with caching and session.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_beaker]pyramid_beaker - A Beaker
       session factory backend for Pyramid, also cache configurator.
          + [http://techspot.zzzeek.org/2012/04/19/using-beaker-for-cachin
            g-why-you-ll-want-to-switch-to-dogpile.cache/]Why You'll Want
            to Switch to dogpile.cache
     * [https://github.com/ericrasmussen/pyramid_redis_sessions]pyramid_re
       dis_sessions - Pyramid web framework session factory backed by
       Redis.
     * [https://github.com/moriyoshi/pyramid_dogpile_cache]pyramid_dogpile
       _cache - dogpile.cache configuration package for Pyramid
     * [https://github.com/joulez/pyramid_sessions]pyramid_sessions -
       Multiple session support for the Pyramid Web Framework
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_nacl_session]pyramid_nacl_sessio
       n - defines an encrypting, pickle-based cookie serializer, using
       [http://pynacl.readthedocs.io/en/latest/secret/]PyNaCl to generate
       the symmetric encryption for the cookie state.

Debugging

   Packages that help hunt down bugs.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_debugtoolbar]pyramid_debugtoolba
       r - provides a debug toolbar useful while you're developing your
       Pyramid application.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_exclog]pyramid_exclog - a
       package which logs exceptions from Pyramid applications.
     * [https://github.com/jvanasco/pyramid_debugtoolbar_dogpile]pyramid_d
       ebugtoolbar_dogpile - dogpile caching support for
       pyramid_debugtoolbar
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_ipython]pyramid_ipython -
       IPython bindings for Pyramid's pshell
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_bpython]pyramid_bpython -
       bpython bindings for Pyramid's pshell
     * [https://github.com/disko/pyramid_pycallgraph]pyramid_pycallgraph -
       Pyramid tween to generate a callgraph image for every request

Email

   Packages that help manage email sending.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_mailer]pyramid_mailer - A
       package for sending email from your Pyramid application.
     * [https://github.com/domenkozar/pyramid_marrowmailer]pyramid_marrowm
       ailer - Pyramid integration package for marrow.mailer, formerly
       known as TurboMail
     * [https://github.com/evannook/pyramid_mailgun]pyramid_mailgun -
       Pyramid integration package for marrow.mailer, formerly known as
       TurboMail

Forms

   Packages that extend the functionality of forms or add new types of
   forms.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/deform]deform - is a Python HTML form
       generation library.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/colander]colander - A
       serialization/deserialization/validation library for strings,
       mappings and lists.
     * [https://github.com/wtforms/wtforms]WTForms - is a flexible forms
       validation and rendering library for python web development.
     * [https://github.com/stefanofontanelli/ColanderAlchemy]ColanderAlche
       my - helps you to auto-generate Colander schemas that are based on
       SQLAlchemy mapped classes.
     * [https://github.com/marshmallow-code/marshmallow]marshmallow - A
       lightweight library for converting complex objects to and from
       simple Python datatypes (i.e. (de)serialization and validation).

Media-Management

     * [https://github.com/uralbash/pyramid_elfinder]pyramid_elfinder -
       This is conector for elfinder file manager, written for pyramid
       framework.
     * [https://github.com/danjac/pyramid_storage]pyramid_storage - This
       is a package for handling file uploads in your Pyramid framework
       application.

RESTful API

   Packages for developing RESTful APIs.
     * [https://github.com/Cornices/cornice]cornice - provides helpers to
       build & document REST-ish Web Services with Pyramid, with decent
       default behaviors. It takes care of following the HTTP
       specification in an automated way where possible.
     * [https://github.com/wichert/rest_toolkit]rest_toolkit - is a Python
       package which provides a very convenient way to build REST servers.
       It is build on top of Pyramid, but you do not need to know much
       about Pyramid to use rest_toolkit.
     * [https://github.com/hadrien/pyramid_royal]pyramid_royal - Royal is
       a pyramid extension which eases writing RESTful web applications.
     * [https://github.com/mozilla-services/cliquet]cliquet - Cliquet is a
       toolkit to ease the implementation of HTTP microservices, such as
       data-driven REST APIs.
     * [https://github.com/sloria/webargs]webargs - A friendly library for
       parsing HTTP request arguments, with built-in support for popular
       web frameworks.
     * [https://github.com/ramses-tech/ramses]ramses - Generate a RESTful
       API using RAML. It uses Nefertari which provides
       ElasticSearch-powered views.
     * [https://github.com/ramses-tech/nefertari]nefertari - Nefertari is
       a REST API framework sitting on top of Pyramid and ElasticSearch
     * [https://github.com/striglia/pyramid_swagger]pyramid_swagger -
       Convenient tools for using Swagger to define and validate your
       interfaces in a Pyramid webapp.
     * [https://github.com/colinhiggs/pyramid-jsonapi]pyramid_jsonapi -
       Automatically create a [http://jsonapi.org/]JSON API standard API
       from a database using the sqlAlchemy ORM and pyramid framework.

Search

   Packages that provide search capabilities to projects.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/hypatia]hypatia - A Python indexing and
       searching system.

Security

   Packages that improve the security of a project.

Services

     * [https://github.com/websauna/pyramid_sms]pyramid_sms - SMS services
       for Pyramid web framework.

Settings

   Packages that help manage the configurability of projects.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_zcml]pyramid_zcml - Zope
       Configuration Markup Language configuration support for Pyramid.
     * [https://github.com/mmerickel/pyramid_services]pyramid_services -
       defines a pattern and helper methods for accessing a pluggable
       service layer from within your Pyramid apps.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/hupper]hupper - A process
       monitor/reloader for developers that can watch files for changes
       and restart the process.

Storage

   Packages that extend the functionality of the existing storage backend
   or provide new storage backends.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_tm]pyramid_tm - Centralized
       transaction management for Pyramid applications (without
       middleware).
     * [https://github.com/zopefoundation/zope.sqlalchemy]zope.sqlalchemy
       - Integration of SQLAlchemy with transaction management.
          + [https://metaclassical.com/what-the-zope-transaction-manager-m
            eans-to-me-and-you/]What the Zope Transaction Manager Means To
            Me (and you)
     * [https://github.com/wichert/pyramid_sqlalchemy]pyramid_sqlalchemy -
       provides some basic glue to facilitate using SQLAlchemy with
       Pyramid.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_zodbconn]pyramid_zodbconn - ZODB
       Database connection management for Pyramid.
     * [https://github.com/marioidival/pyramid_mongoengine]pyramid_mongoen
       gine - pyramid-mongoengine package based on flask-mongoengine
     * [https://github.com/niallo/pyramid_mongodb]pyramid_mongodb - Basic
       Pyramid Scaffold to easily use MongoDB for persistence with the
       Pyramid Web framework
     * [https://github.com/pyexcel-webwares/pyramid-excel]pyramid-excel -
       pyramid-excel is based on
       [https://github.com/pyexcel/pyexcel]pyexcel and makes it easy to
       consume/produce information stored in excel files over HTTP
       protocol as well as on file system. This library can turn the excel
       data into a list of lists, a list of records(dictionaries),
       dictionaries of lists. And vice versa. Hence it lets you focus on
       data in Pyramid based web development, instead of file formats.

Task Queue

   Packages that make working with task/background queues easier.
     * [https://github.com/sontek/pyramid_celery]pyramid_celery - Pyramid
       configuration with celery integration. Allows you to use pyramid
       .ini files to configure celery and have your pyramid configuration
       inside celery tasks.
     * [https://github.com/wichert/pyramid_rq]pyramid_rq - Support using
       the rq queueing system with pyramid. The easiest way to monitor and
       use [http://python-rq.org/]RQ in your Pyramid projects.

Templates

     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_mako]pyramid_mako - Mako
       templating system bindings for the Pyramid web framework.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_chameleon]pyramid_chameleon -
       Chameleon template compiler for pyramid.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_jinja2]pyramid_jinja2 - Jinja2
       templating system bindings for the Pyramid web framework.
     * [https://github.com/ztane/Tonnikala]Tonnikala - Python templating
       engine with Pyramid integration
     * [https://github.com/nandoflorestan/kajiki]Kajiki - provides fast
       well-formed XML templates, with
       [https://github.com/nandoflorestan/kajiki/blob/master/kajiki/integr
       ation/pyramid.py]Pyramid integration

Testing

   Packages that help test code or generate test data.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/webtest]webtest - Wraps any WSGI
       application and makes it easy to send test requests to that
       application, without starting up an HTTP server.

Translations

   Packages help with the task of translating projects.
     * [https://github.com/wichert/lingua]lingua - Lingua is a package
       with tools to extract translatable texts from your code, and to
       check existing translations. It replaces the use of the xgettext
       command from gettext, or pybabel from Babel.
     * [https://github.com/sahama/pyramid_i18n_helper]pyramid_i18n_helper
       - helper to create new smgid and translate msgid to local langs .

Web frontend integration

     * [https://github.com/eddyekofo94/pyramidVue]PyramidVue - Pyramid and
       VueJs (JavaScript) template with Hot-Module-Replacement starter
       template.

Workflows

   Packages that do process, procedure and/or business tasks management.

Other

     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_layout]pyramid_layout - Pyramid
       add-on for managing UI layouts.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_skins]pyramid_skins - This
       package provides a simple framework to integrate code with
       templates and resources.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/waitress]waitress - Waitress is meant to
       be a production-quality pure-Python WSGI server with very
       acceptable performance. It has no dependencies except ones which
       live in the Python standard library.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_handlers]pyramid_handlers -
       analogue of Pylons-style "controllers" for Pyramid.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_rpc]pyramid_rpc - RPC service
       add-on for Pyramid, supports XML-RPC in a more extensible manner
       than pyramid_xmlrpc with support for JSON-RPC and AMF.
     * [https://github.com/SurveyMonkey/pyramid_autodoc]pyramid_autodoc -
       Sphinx extension for documenting your Pyramid APIs.
     * [https://github.com/uralbash/pyramid_pages]pyramid_pages - Provides
       a collections of tree pages to your Pyramid application. This is
       very similar to django.contrib.flatpages but with a tree structure
       and traversal algorithm in URL dispath.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/paginate]paginate - Python pagination
       module.
     * [https://github.com/lxneng/pyramid_tablib]pyramid_tablib - tablib
       renderer (xlsx, xls, csv) for pyramid
     * [https://github.com/sontek/tomb_routes]tomb_routes - Simple utility
       library around pyramid routing
     * [https://github.com/jenner/pyramid_extdirect]pyramid_extdirect -
       This pyramid plugin provides a router for the ExtDirect Sencha API
       included in ExtJS. ExtDirect allows to run server-side callbacks
       directly through JavaScript without the extra AJAX boilerplate.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/pyramid_retry]pyramid_retry -
       pyramid_retry is an execution policy for Pyramid that wraps
       requests and can retry them a configurable number of times under
       certain "retryable" error conditions before indicating a failure to
       the client.

Projects

   Outstanding Pyramid projects.

Framework

     * [http://www.ringo-framework.org/]Ringo - Ringo is a Python based
       high level web application framework build on top of Pyramid. The
       framework can be used to build form based management or
       administration software.
     * [https://github.com/bluedynamics/cone.app]cone.app - A
       comprehensive web application stub on top of Pyramid.

CMS

     * [https://github.com/nive/nive_cms]nive_cms - Nive is professional
       out the box content management system for mobile and desktop
       websites based on python and the webframework pyramid. Please refer
       to the website cms.nive.co for detailed information.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/substanced]substanced - An application
       server built upon the Pyramid web framework. It provides a user
       interface for managing content as well as libraries and utilities
       which make it easy to create applications.
     * [https://github.com/Kotti/Kotti]Kotti - A user-friendly,
       light-weight and extensible web content management system. Based on
       Pyramid and SQLAlchemy.
     * [https://karlproject.readthedocs.io/en/latest/]KARL - A
       moderately-sized application (roughly 80K lines of Python code)
       built on top of Pyramid. It is an open source web system for
       collaboration, organizational intranets, and knowledge management.
       It provides facilities for wikis, calendars, manuals, searching,
       tagging, commenting, and file uploads. See the KARL site for
       download and installation details.

Cookiecutters

     * [https://github.com/Pylons?q=cookiecutter]Pylons - official
       cookiecutter templates
     * [https://github.com/asif-mahmud/pyramid_runner]Pyramid Runner - A
       minimal Pyramid scaffold that aims to provide a starter template to
       build small to large web services.
          + Traversal based application
          + JSON only response
          + JWT authentication policy
          + Alembic for database revisions
          + Some simple modifications to base tests, views and models base
            to reduce typing

e-Commerce

Other

     * [https://github.com/Pylons/cluegun]cluegun - A simple pastebin
       application based on Rocky Burt's ClueBin. It demonstrates form
       processing, security, and the use of ZODB within a Pyramid
       application.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/shootout]shootout - An example "idea
       competition" application by Carlos de la Guardia and Lukasz Fidosz.
       It demonstrates URL dispatch, simple authentication, integration
       with SQLAlchemy and pyramid_simpleform.
     * [https://github.com/Pylons/virginia]virginia - A very simple
       dynamic file rendering application. It is willing to render
       structured text documents, HTML documents, and images from a
       filesystem directory. It's also a good example of traversal. An
       earlier version of this application runs the repoze.org website.
     * [https://docs.pylonsproject.org/projects/akhet/en/latest/]Akhet - A
       Pyramid library and demo application with a Pylons-like feel. Its
       most known for its former application scaffold, which helped users
       transition from Pylons and those preferring a more Pylons-like API.
       The scaffold has been retired but the demo plays a similar role.
     * [http://khufuproject.github.io/]Khufu Project - Khufu is an
       application scaffolding for Pyramid that provides an environment to
       work with Jinja2 and SQLAlchemy.
     * [https://github.com/ptahproject/ptah]Ptah - Ptah is a fast, fun,
       open source high-level Python web development environment.
     * [https://github.com/pypa/warehouse]warehouse - Warehouse is a next
       generation Python Package Repository designed to replace the legacy
       code base that currently powers PyPI.
     * [https://github.com/mazvv/travelcrm]travelcrm - TravelCRM is
       effective free and open source application for the automation of
       customer relationships for travel agencies at all levels, from
       small to large networks.
     * [https://rhodecode.com/]RhodeCode - enterprise source code
       management platform. It applies unified user control, permissions,
       code reviews, and tool integration across Mercurial, Git, and
       Subversion repositories. Large and growing software teams all over
       the world use RhodeCode to collaborate in a secure,
       behind-the-firewall environment.

Project Management

     * [https://getappenlight.com/]AppEnlight - Performance, exception,
       and uptime monitoring for the Web

Resources

   Where to discover new Pyramid apps and projects.

Books

     * [http://www.oreilly.com/web-platform/free/python-web-frameworks.csp
       ]Python Web Frameworks - Dive into details on the top six Python
       frameworks--Django, Flask, Tornado, Bottle, Pyramid, and CherryPy.

Websites

     * [https://trypyramid.com/]Try Pyramid - The Start Small, Finish Big,
       Stay Finished Framework. Official website.

Conferences

     * [https://pyconweb.com/talks/28-05-2017/pyramid-workshop]Pyramid
       Workshop in Munich, Germany. (May 28, 2017, 10:30 a.m. - 12:30
       p.m.)
     * [https://2017.ploneconf.org/]PloneConf 2017 - Barcelona Plone
       Digital Experience Conference (16~22 Oct. 2017)
